

Use terminal to run both programs.

Call 'make' to build the executables.

To run the server:
                   ./server [port number]
(you may choose any port number above 1024)

To run the client:
                   ./client [host name] [port number]
(host name can be either IP address or name of host you want to connec to)
(port number is the port that is used by the server)

Example: If you want to run it on just one computer
1. Open 2 terminals
2. Run the server.                                 ./server 12222
3. On a different terminal, run the client.        ./client localhost 12222
4. Enter a message and press 'Enter'.
5. To close the server, press "CTRL-C"